trying to increase

00:35:02.260 --> 00:35:03.680
the supply of great options.

00:35:03.680 --> 00:35:06.010
So we just showed you
snippets out of two models.

00:35:06.010 --> 00:35:08.427
But we're trying to increase
the supply of options of what

00:35:08.427 --> 00:35:10.180
we call catalytic models--

00:35:10.180 --> 00:35:12.478
models that are getting
great results-- not just

00:35:12.478 --> 00:35:14.020
academic results,
but the other kinds

00:35:14.020 --> 00:35:15.550
of results that we were
just talking about.

00:35:15.550 --> 00:35:17.620
Sometimes we talk about
the triple wow factor.

00:35:17.620 --> 00:35:20.677
So one wow is kids
wow-- like, wow,

00:35:20.677 --> 00:35:23.010
I cannot wait to come to
school, I cannot wait to learn,

00:35:23.010 --> 00:35:24.130
this is exciting.

00:35:24.130 --> 00:35:25.610
A second wow is
the families' wow--

00:35:25.610 --> 00:35:27.610
like, this is so good for
my kid, I love my kid,

00:35:27.610 --> 00:35:29.860
my kid is loved, they are
growing, they're challenged,

00:35:29.860 --> 00:35:30.940
it's rigorous.

00:35:30.940 --> 00:35:34.120
And the third is educators,
because the traditional design

00:35:34.120 --> 00:35:36.080
of school is not easy
for educators, as well.

00:35:36.080 --> 00:35:38.705
So if we can create models that
are getting verified results

00:35:38.705 --> 00:35:40.330
but also having this
triple wow factor,

00:35:40.330 --> 00:35:43.025
that's one piece of what
we call a catalytic model.

00:35:43.025 --> 00:35:45.010
A second is that
it sparks demand.

00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:46.960
And so all of these
examples, and many others

00:35:46.960 --> 00:35:49.000
that we work with, people
see them and they say,

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:50.708
we want that in our
communities, as well.

00:35:50.708 --> 00:35:53.430
And so that's part of
creating the wave of change,

00:35:53.430 --> 00:35:55.090
to accelerate it, to your point.

00:35:55.090 --> 00:35:57.110
And the third are,
can they be codified

00:35:57.110 --> 00:35:58.360
in ways that make it sharable?

00:35:58.360 --> 00:36:00.460
So to the point of, even
all those little rituals

00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:02.620
and different things like that,
someone had to think them up.

00:36:02.620 --> 00:36:03.640
Someone had to write them down.

00:36:03.640 --> 00:36:05.170
Someone had to try
them, et cetera.

00:36:05.170 --> 00:36:06.340
There's no reason
